THOUGHT: The crash indicates an insertelement/shufflevector is created at a point that doesn't dominate all its uses. SLPVectorizer.cpp has a CreateInsertElement lambda around line 13992 and uses Builder.CreateInsertElement around line 14020. A minimal fix is to set the IRBuilder insertion point to a safe location that dominates operands, e.g., at the first non-PHI in the parent block of the vector operand when it's an instruction, before creating the insertelement. I'll patch SLPVectorizer.cpp to set Builder.SetInsertPoint appropriately right before Builder.CreateInsertElement within that lambda, then build and test.

```bash
nl -ba llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp | sed -n '13980,14040p' && python3 - <<'PY'
import re
p='llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp'
s=open(p).read()
# Inject a dominance-safe insertion point before the CreateInsertElement call inside the lambda
s=re.sub(r'(Vec\s*=\s*Builder\.CreateInsertElement\(Vec,\s*Scalar,\s*Builder\.getInt32\(Pos\)\);)',
         r'''{
  if (auto *InstVec = dyn_cast<Instruction>(Vec)) {
    if (BasicBlock *BB = InstVec->getParent()) {
      Instruction *IP = BB->getFirstNonPHI();
      if (IP) Builder.SetInsertPoint(IP);
    }
  }
  \1
}''', s)
open(p,'w').write(s)
print('Patched insertion point in',p)
PY
 && ninja -C build/llvm-build/127128 -j2 llvm-opt 2>&1 | sed -n '1,120p' && ./build/llvm-build/127128/bin/opt -S --passes=slp-vectorizer -mtriple=x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu -mcpu=haswell /tmp/test.ll 2>&1 | sed -n '1,120p' && submit-patch```

